translated: Dymling, Carl Johan, licentiate in theology, former lecturer, born on December 11th, 1880 in Gothenburg to Swen Joh. D. and Anna Cecilia Cavalli, who was a merchant. Married to Marta Hen-rich in 1911. Children: Harry Eduard born in 1912 and Mary Karin born in 1914. He passed his studentexamen in Gothenburg in 1899, became a filosofie kandidat in theology in Gothenburg in 1902, teologie kandidat in Lund in 1910, and received an honorary doctorate in theology in Erlangen (equivalent to a Swedish royal decree) in 1917. Dymling went on a study trip to Rostock in 1907, Berlin, Leipzig and Marburg in 1909. He became an extra assistant teacher in Sundsvall from 1911-1915, extra lecturer in Skövde from 1915-1917, curate in Kungsholms parish in Stockholm from 1917-1921, acting curate in Bromma parish from 1921-1925, substitute curate in Högalid's parish from 1925-1926, in St. Göran's parish from 1926-1927, and a teacher in Östersund from 1929-1932. Lastly, he was a lecturer in Christian art at Halmstad's high school from 1931-1946. Dymling's written works include Kyrkan o. teol. (08), Vår tids lyckosträvan (13), Barnasjälen o. dess vård (15), Själens krafter (16), Martin Luther (17), Blödande hjärtan (17), Carlyle (18), Krav o. kraft (18), Mystiker (20), Drömliv o. dröm-forskn. (20), Kvinnors själsliv (23), Mysteriet människan (29), Den levande själen (33), Kampen om människovärdet (39), Människan o. hennes öde (40), Tro o. trots i Martin Luthers liv (46), articles in Swedish and German newspapers and journals.
